article.headline: Old Dominion 56, Delaware 49
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Gerald Lee scored 16 points to lead Old Dominion to a 56-49 victory over Delaware on Saturday. Keyon Carter added 13 points for Old Dominion (3-3, 1-0 Colonial Athletic Association), which led by 22 points with 7:06 remaining in the game. The Monarchs held a 21-point advantage with 3:08 left before the Blue Hens (2-6, 0-1) attempted a rally to cut the lead to 53-46 on Jawan Carter's 3-pointer with 30 seconds remaining. Jawan Carter, who led Delaware with 21 points, hit another 3-pointer to chop the lead to 55-49 with 11 seconds left, but that was as close as the Blue Hens would get. Old Dominion didn't make a field goal in the final 3:08 of the game. Marc Egerson had 12 rebounds for Delaware.
